# 🔍 Nessus Vulnerability Scanner in Docker

![Docker](https://img.shields.io/badge/Docker-Ready-blue?logo=docker)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green?logo=open-source-initiative)
![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/Status-Stable-brightgreen?logo=checkmarx)

> 🚀 A lightweight, containerized setup for Tenable Nessus – the industry-standard vulnerability scanner. Deploy in seconds, scan in minutes.

---

## 📦 Features

- 🐳 **Dockerized**: Run Nessus in an isolated container
- 🔐 **Secure**: HTTPS access on port `8834`
- 🔄 **Auto Plugin Updates**: Keep your scanner fresh
- 🧪 **Easy Testing**: Scan local or remote targets with ease

---

## ⚙️ Installation

```bash
docker pull treadie/nessus
docker run -d --name nessus -p 8834:8834 treadie/nessus



🌐 Access
Open your browser and go to:
https://localhost:8834


Then:
- Register with your activation code
- Update plugins
- Start scanning!

